Pours a clear reddish amber with a frothy, foamy head that settles into a thin sudsy lacing. It has aromas of lightly toasted grains, a apple and grape fruitiness with a little orange zest, earthy yeast, and a soft floral hoppiness. 

Pleasant tasting, toasted grassy grains and caramelized sugary maltiness, earthy, peppery yeastiness, a light fruitiness, a bit apple and orange, spicy hops with a soft, but lingering bitterness, a slight taste of alcohol towards the end, the alcohol provides a subtle warming in the palate, and a dry grainy, subtle fruity, spicy finish.

Ice wine is a type of dessert wine produced from grapes that have been frozen while still on the vine. This results in a smaller amount of more concentrated, very sweet wine. Due to the labour-intense and risky production process resulting in relatively small amounts of wine, ice wines are generally quite expensive.

Each player has one chair and sets it in a row with their opponents' chairs. Players take turns with an attempt to break their opponents' chair. The player with their chair left standing is the winner. There are two versions of 'Fat Arse'.

General Rules
1) Chairs = Number of players are set up in a row.
2) Slings and bullets are provided. All players must use the same sling and ammunition to break the opponent's chairs.
3) If you fire more than once on your turn, you miss out on the next number of turns of additional fires.

Luck Fat Arse
Players use dice to determine which chair they have to hit. This could result in a player breaking their own chair.

Grudge Fat Arse
Players choose whose chair they will hit. A game of loyalties, betrayal and tactics!

There are two mini-forts for 'Capture the Flag' games. The aim of this game is to retrieve a flag of your opponents' team and bring it back to your team's base. Get creative and use the environment, utilities and obstacles we've provided to form offensive and defensive tactics!

Setting up
1. Split into two teams and go to your team's base.
2. You are given time to prepare. During this time, each team is given 3-5 flags to set down on their own base so the other team can retrieve them.
3. Once preparation time is up, you can begin the game.

General Rules	
1. You're not allowed to spy on your opponents' team during preparation time.
2. When retrieving the opponents' team flag, you MUST holster the flag on your back when returning it back to your base. Instead of picking up a flag from an unconscious ally, you have to go to your opponents base to retrieve another one (which is why each team must set a number of flags in their own base during preparation time so that the other team can retrieve them).
3. You cannot hide or sneak when carrying your opponents' flag and you cannot be under the effects of ethereal when carrying them (this includes haven and greater sanctuary)
4. Flying and 'Shadow Jumping' are allowed.
5. Potions, scrolls, traps and other gadgets are allowed but will not be compensated for its use.
6. Using barricades, or other objects and spell walls to block an area is banned.
7. No acts of killing
8. If you're participating in these events please do not go to the lounging area and bar, we hope to keep that area tidy and safe for those not participating.

Turn-Based Capture the Flag	
For a less chaotic and structured game, where both teams take turns to capture the flag whilst the other team defends. A capturing team loses the round if they fail to bring the opponent's team flag back to their base or the whole party is taken out. 

All-Out Capture the Flag	
This is where both teams try to get the opponent's team flag simultaenously in one game. The first team to have an opponents flag in their own base wins.
